The calibration procedure of the RDS-DP follows the same methodology applied for previous Mars’ radiometers developed by INTA (Jimenez et al. 2018) which is based on the spectroradiometric transfer, from a standard lamp to a detector, in well-controlled laboratory conditions. In these conditions, the calibration model assumes that the wavelength, the temperature and the relative position of the incident light can be considered as independent variables and, therefore, the output signal of every optical channel can be expressed as: I(T,φ,θ,ESun)=ARF(θ,φ)⋅TRF(T)⋅Rλ1Sunλ2⋅Eλ1Sunλ2+offset(T)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
