Finally, the ARF calibration is performed in a dark room facility of SPASOLAB, maintaining a constant ambient temperature and using a stable Xenon lamp situated far enough from the sensor (around 4,5 m) to obtain a uniform plane of light. The RDS is installed then in a robotic 2-axis platform (0,01∘ precision each) that allows to situate each detector at any angle with respect to the light beam. A series of sweeps in the zenith and azimuthal coordinates are performed around the normal to each detector while RDS is measuring. An example of the data obtained is shown in Fig. 42, where the values are normalized to the maximum reached in the center of each channel. Fig. 42
