The accuracy is estimated to be <10%. Include something related to the laser test showing no stray light. The relative uncertainty budget, comparing 1 pixel of a typical image to another pixel of another image, is:
Measurement uncertainty of 0.25% based on SNR after dark subtraction;
Temperature correction uncertainty <1%;
Linearity, 0.1%;
Flat field knowledge, <1% for central FoV, <2% for exterior annulus.

The absolute uncertainty budget is:
Uncertainty in the light source, 2%;
Uncertainty in color temperature of the light source, convolved with the camera bandpass, 2.75%;

