In both case, the acquisition strategy consists of capturing two images in a row, one with an exposure time of 0 seconds (dark image), and other with the commanded exposure time. Both images will be stored in the instrument memory, and subsequently sent to the rover for automatic subtraction, thus generating a single 1024×1024\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
